Record_Notes:
Width not clear as the covered shed cuts through the centre of the wall. Measurements appear to be (when combined with the 1950 Boon plan) are 0.66m, 0.60m, 1.01m from E - W. Note that the W end is curved into the apse.

East end butts with M.036.

This would have had the entrance to R01, Boon notes it as being directly opposite the entrance between R03-R02 some 0.63m from the N/E corner of R03. No obvious evidence remains of this, however.

Arch roughly 0.76m from the E corner connects the hypocaust between R01 and R02. This consists of a corbled arch. Arch begins at 0.42m above current floor surface and angles inwards through two/three courses of blockwork before being capped with a flat lintel at 0.70m
